gomodel:SYNGO_3089  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 1 Legend, panels C-G:\n\nLiteral: \" (C and D) The membrane extracts (1 mg proteins) from the cortex of mice 2 hr after sham (lane 1) or MCAO (lane 2) were precipitated with nonspecific IgG (IgG) or anti-NR2B (C) or anti-DAPK1 (D) and probed with anti-DAPK1, anti-NR1, anti-PSD95 or anti-NR2B. Input: 20 mg of protein was loaded in each lane except the PSD95 lane, in which 10 mg proteins were loaded.\n(E-G) DAPK1+/+ (E) and DAPK1 / (G) cultured neurons were stained with anti-DAPK1 (red) and anti-NR2B (green). A high magnified image (F) from a selected area in (E). In panels A-G, similar results were observed in each of the four experiments.\". Experimental description: Methods section: Cell Cultures and Oxygen-Glucose Deprivation\n\nLiteral: \"Hippocampi were isolated from the E20 DAPK1 mice. Cells were dissociated and purified using papain dissociation kit...\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-6893-6177" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-5265-6306" ;
        dc:date           "2018-04-09" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_3089" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

